article.headline: Yale 98, Allegheny 55
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Eric Flato scored 15 points and Jason Abromaitis recorded career high's with 12 points and 11 rebounds as Yale routed Division III Allegheny 98-55 Sunday in the season opener for both teams. Abromaitis, whose father, Jim, was a standout at the University of Connecticut from 1975-80, made five-of-seven shots and also had four offensive rebounds. Sophomore guard Travis Pinick added 14 points, all in the second half, while making his first career start for the Bulldogs, who were without injured starters Casey Hughes and Ross Morin. Yale led 32-18 at the half before shooting a sizzling 61.5 percent from the field (24-for-39) in the second half. The Bulldogs scored 66 second-half points pushed the lead past 40 points on several occasions before holding a game-high 46-point advantage in the closing minutes. Freshman forward George Raftis scored 14 points and eight rebounds for Allegheny.
